Feedback:
The switch operated as expected:

1. When closed, a continuity test between the switch ports resulted in a very low resistance (0.01 Ω), indicating an intact, conductive path.
2. When opened, the same continuity test detected a very high resistance (~998 MΩ), indicating no conductive path.

These results confirm there is no evidence of a 'SwitchInternalFault' at this time. The switch opens and closes as intended, making and breaking continuity reliably. No anomalous behavior was observed.
